# MD Import Force - Project Overview

This WordPress plugin allows for importing content with specific IDs. The main entry point is [md-import-force.php](mdc:md-import-force.php), which initializes the plugin.

## Main File Structure

- [md-import-force.php](mdc:md-import-force.php) - Main plugin file with plugin definitions and initialization
- [includes/](mdc:includes) - Core PHP classes for plugin functionality
- [templates/](mdc:templates) - Admin interface templates
- [assets/](mdc:assets) - JavaScript and CSS files
- [logs/](mdc:logs) - Error and activity logs

## Key Components

- Plugin Initialization: [class-md-import-force-initializer.php](mdc:includes/class-md-import-force-initializer.php)
- Admin Interface: [admin-page.php](mdc:templates/admin-page.php)
- JavaScript Core: [index.js](mdc:assets/js/admin/index.js) loads all client-side modules

## WordPress Integration Notes

- WordPress Core Functions: Functions like `plugin_dir_path()`, `add_action()`, `__()`, `wp_enqueue_script()`, etc. are native WordPress functions and do not need to be defined in this project.
- These functions are available automatically when the plugin is loaded in WordPress.
- Linter errors for these functions in standalone IDE environments can be ignored.

